skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "507e1e09-7f64-4378-a809-5f9e58d5b99c", "value": "The extraction of natural resources/geological materials i.e. metals, stone etc. from the earth by excavating pits or trenches into the surface."}

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "3417ad18-c25f-45db-91ec-c6ca61e5efd5", "value": "Enhanced Protection List of the Hague Convention"}
{"id": "e07a4028-cd43-4926-a756-2cc44027e16c", "value": "Aerial Photographic Archive for Archaeology in the Middle East (APAAME)"}
{"id": "65615354-c051-487e-822d-a2dd7f0b99b8", "value": "United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO)"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "83334e6e-d83f-41c4-99a9-1c810d190e52", "value": "The effects of water on archaeological features and sites, this includes rising damp, structural decay, rotting, rusting etc."}

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "03e6a688-5b46-414b-a094-eef61c615d95", "value": "Sir Aurel Stein Archive, The British Academy Library and Archive"}
{"id": "f262fb63-3056-46f9-a53f-77c5a749f939", "value": "Aerial Photographic Archive for Archaeology in the Middle East (APAAME)"}
{"id": "89b8ed32-6577-4372-8e6a-7037a0656d36", "value": "Air Survey Photographs, UCL Institute of Archaeology Special Collections"}
{"id": "c96ab4e6-512e-4dc8-ad30-7026e23cdbfe", "value": "CORONA Atlas of the Middle East, Center for Advanced Spatial Technologies, University of Arkansas"}
{"id": "089e3360-9a9b-445e-a969-277765809987", "value": "Historic Environment Image Resource, University of Oxford (HEIR)"}
{"id": "3e920696-cae5-43f0-adf6-cd8643e57778", "value": "Endangered Archaeology in the Middle East and North Africa (EAMENA)"}

skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "9b9bd0e0-fe9a-42ae-a260-8ad368954342", "value": "Sudden movement/vibrations of the earth's crust e.g. earthquakes"}
{"id": "08c5b7cf-cd94-4bdb-9eef-13cbf6a2bdfc", "value": "The artificial and deliberate provision of water by the means of pipes, sprinklers, drains, ditches etc."}
{"id": "c753b7e3-e492-4c6a-82f2-e78212c9f1c6", "value": "An explosive charge laid on or just under a surface (anthropogenic or natural)"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "2feeec4e-39b3-4b5f-93a1-18c98f64c561", "value": "A non-electronic optical instrument for surveying and measurement of levels, distances, and slopes"}

{"id": "c8460966-dec7-45c9-bf73-3a74377ac4e5", "value": "Satellite imagery are images of Earth or other planets collected by imaging satellites operated by governments and businesses around the world. This category only applies to unprocessed satellite imagery tiles."}

skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "a253c22b-9092-4369-8d14-c4903862092a", "value": "The collapse/movement of a mass of earth or rock, generally down a slope."}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "cf53dcad-adc0-470c-8093-bd39b6c26895", "value": "Social factors that contribute to deterioration processes of the fabric of heritage sites. Some uses might have a positive impact as they enhance certain values (e.g. ritual, religious) while others might compromise ascribed values and could lead to the deterioration of the heritage site."}

skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "7fac1d35-d694-4a76-a610-70f98e06945b", "value": "The contamination of the land, water, air etc., by the presence or introduction of poisioness or harmful substances. This can cover pollution arising from natural disasters, as well as pollution caused by dense urbanization etc."}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "86f3306d-ed88-49b6-b14d-ee8a59484aee", "value": "Satellite imagery are images of Earth or other planets collected by imaging satellites operated by governments and businesses around the world. Processing may include georectification, orthorectification, atmosphere correction."}

skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "c4f68f47-3ed4-4002-918a-3d351186dcbb", "value": "The act of digging or creating a hole/trench with heavy duty machinery for a purpose other than mining/quarrying. This term can be used to cover archaeological excavation or excavation for the purposes of looting."}

{"id": "2d8e7fa5-90d6-4c1f-a0e6-9c9ed88cb46e", "value": "The act of destruction or tearing down of archaeological structures. This act can be carried out both in a controlled and uncontrolled manner, but also using both mechanised and/or hand machinery"}

{"id": "ba8541a9-006e-4d8a-b8b8-8ea538f5516a", "value": "The act of clearing and/or flattening/destroying ground or archaeological features/modern buildings etc., where it is not clear whether this has been carried out using mechanised machinery or by hand."}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "6f582ba5-54fb-47d6-8d60-33f8d594a7c4", "value": "Emission of energy in forms of waves or particles, e.g. sunlight."}

{"id": "2b6ad209-4676-4b19-ade6-ec17d2f8506a", "value": "Removal of non-structural items (for structural use structural robbing) e.g immovable objects, site panels or signage. Note: use Excavation linked to looting when looters holes are seen but do not definitely know that material has been removed from the site."}

skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "b2f95b6a-44d9-4bfb-b6ce-35a0d7ea667b", "value": "The violent discharge of steam/volcanic material from an active vent in the earth's crust"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "98cb4db9-ad3d-429f-9982-c8a36da3dbff", "value": "A prolonged period of abnormally low rainfall, leading to a shortage of water; for heritage sites the decreased humidity can cause structural and other problems. For normally submerged sites use \"Recession of water\"."}

skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "40b76f9b-d7cc-4d48-9adb-65cdc8dad446", "value": "The presence of anthropogenically planted and/or managed orchards, forests and/or woods (silviculture)."}

{"id": "674f7f54-525d-4c9d-a3a1-276e846236ea", "value": "The condensation of water vapour in the earth's atmosphere which leads to water falling in the form of rain, snow, sleet etc. and being deposited on the earth's surface."}

{"id": "33f5e7c1-fbf0-4213-a689-86f14b13fd78", "value": "Presence of non-moving objects used in transport e.g. cars, tanks etc., at a site. For example, the presence of stationary tanks may indicate that the site is under military control."}

{"id": "fb917144-6425-4ac2-abc9-a04b58c02ed4", "value": "The act of digging or creating a hole/trench for a purpose other than mining/quarrying where it is not clear whether this has been carried out using mechanised machinery or by hand. This term can be used to cover archaeological excavation or excavation for the purposes of looting."}

{"id": "640a0a4e-4f40-49e3-9f31-6a2bb9409750", "value": "This term covers a series of effects (e.g. erosion/weathering) which are caused by the flow and movement of bodies of water (i.e. sea, lake, river, 'wadi'). It does not include flooding and precipitation which are listed as separate causes."}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "81fb5a11-95e8-4134-ad9e-f272587986dc", "value": "The act of people moving across a heritage site, which can cause damage to the features and erosion."}

skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "c9f4eb19-c4c2-4fce-9aa8-452a509f08eb", "value": "The act of writing or drawing (can be scratched, painted etc.) something onto a surface. In this case the surface of an archaeological object, feature or site."}

{"id": "a79b394c-e5f0-4f2c-9f13-b0506a86af13", "value": "The delibreate act of changing the contours of the land/earth's surface. This can include landscaping in order to produce terraces, as well as the deposition of imported soil, raising the level of land surface/"}

{"id": "7ecc9f60-6588-4c01-8686-5156295a9ea4", "value": "The act of trying to keep archaeological sites in good condition, possibly through the addition of modern features, such as walkways etc. on a heritage site. This does not include conservation."}

{"id": "30e3a21d-b29d-4dc2-93ef-733eb1264f4a", "value": "An anthropogenic act involving an area being covered/overwhelmed with water. This is differentiated from flooding by being defined as a deliberate and anthropogenic act."}
{"id": "dd064e29-6db2-485e-8ebc-dbf9a76e49c4", "value": "The act of removing material (e.g. stone/mudbrick) from an archaeological site. "}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "efb042cc-7bff-42e2-a242-ba6d5a9bd516", "value": "To only include activities which do not fall under construction e.g. adding electricity, painting, replacing old water pipes"}

skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "b304c470-1b1d-4d72-8053-390dc602ba73", "value": "The act of living, inhabiting or continuing to utilise a certain place"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "ba9828b7-e58e-43e9-a322-239bbdbe2895", "value": "Lowering or complete disappearance of the surface elevation of a lake or other water body (e.g. sea)."}

skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "040d3908-959d-4402-bc32-3d95146c64bb", "value": "The extraction of natural resources/geological materials i.e. metals, stone etc. from the earth by excavating under the surface of the ground, accessed through tunnels, shafts, or caves."}
{"id": "6aa7e211-ce6a-486a-b7b0-393b0ac630be", "value": "The act of animals consuming vegetation/and or being moved across an area of land whether that vegetation be natural or planted."}
{"id": "9c72d843-c41e-4b7c-ba66-1eb36d060c89", "value": "A path or route leading from one place to another, often including a built or anthropogenically modified/altered surface "}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "8d3f7543-6964-4901-a15a-ef812ec37f50", "value": "This term covers a series of effects (e.g. erosion/weathering) which are caused by the flow and movement of bodies of water (i.e. sea, lake, river, 'wadi') and/or by the flow and movement of the wind, but where it is uncertain which of the two or both were responsible."}

{"id": "54db5367-889e-4bad-b50a-b8364a716b93", "value": "Salt dissolved in groundwater (or sometimes water from the air) raising up and recrystallizing in heritage features such as buildings or rock surfaces."}

{"id": "667d6ab2-6b46-4c6c-a990-8adca18fd8c0", "value": "Restoration means returning a place to a known earlier state by removing accretions or by reassembling existing elements without the introduction of new material."}

skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "66407f40-da32-47f5-8941-2d73e532ce09", "value": "The extraction of natural resources/geological materials i.e. metals, stone etc. from the earth, by unknown means"}

{"id": "056ba5cb-2f8f-4a1e-b15b-3fc948c1a487", "value": "This term covers a series of effects (e.g. erosion/weathering) which are caused by the flow and movement of the wind. It does not include temperature and humidity changes which are listed as a separate cause."}
{"id": "488d7004-a93b-4e8d-8e9e-31172c139ace", "value": "An exothermic process involving the oxidation of material, sending out light and heat and possibly producing smoke."}
{"id": "4960c0f0-6e83-4dac-92f7-1f2b538b1699", "value": "The installation and use of a centre pivot irrigation system for the provision of water to an area."}

{"id": "b918f1f5-1700-4b2f-b1c7-0886c1100489", "value": "The act of building, including structures, such as housing, infrastructure etc., and the resulting product/s. These activities can be on an industrial/public scale, or at a much smaller 'domestic' scale."}

{"id": "cfed9fce-ef97-4546-b3c7-2ed403465b1e", "value": "The act of creating/digging a usually narrow passage or channel through earth/rock. This process can be connected with mining activities and the construction of hydrological features."}
{"id": "52e6c62c-b007-494c-9e75-fe65293d0137", "value": "The act of clearing and/or flattening/destroying ground or archaeological features/modern buildings etc., using mechanised machinery."}

{"id": "18d0f3ac-309d-4763-9b32-b534f4162f88", "value": "Shifts in the environmental conditions at a site/of a feature. This definition would include changes in moisture content at both a local and regional level, as well as shifts in the comparative scales of hot and cold."}

{"id": "3f910f93-ac46-4098-adfb-255cf6db731d", "value": "The extraction of natural resources/geological materials i.e. metals, stone etc. from the earth by scraping or working the surface of the ground, often with machinery such as bulldozers. Most often in alluvial contexts."}
{"id": "a616f965-e14e-4094-a15e-8f000fba7757", "value": "The act of turning/breaking up the earth, predominantly in preparation for the planting of crops. "}
{"id": "700582f9-43a1-45ed-84e6-c7ba04102657", "value": "The act of clearing and/or flattening/destroying ground or archaeological features/modern buildings etc., by hand/using handtools."}
{"id": "f5be7d76-6537-4eaf-972a-851c23067a7d", "value": "The action of disposing of unwanted material, including scrap material and waste."}

{"id": "1c044bf9-821e-42f5-9196-3e6b9a6f5de0", "value": "The act of digging or creating a hole/trench by hand/hand tools for a purpose other than mining/quarrying. This term can be used to cover archaeological excavation or excavation for the purposes of looting."}

{"id": "50f8b07f-b273-4601-88f9-f6231b8c31c5", "value": "This term should be used to indicate that, given the current evidence, there is no evidence for damage and/or threat to the archaeological site mentioned in published imagery or identifiable from imagery sources."}
{"id": "9b5af1e0-733a-4af0-9c54-ed0fffec1b72", "value": "The release of energy in an often sudden and violent way. This can lead to the sudden shattering or blowing apart of objects/features."}
{"id": "b0204b4a-fdcd-4c44-ae10-aff7f911fb6f", "value": "The act of digging trenches across a landscape and the provision of water through that system to an area."}

{"id": "5fd2e9ab-6c37-4a87-a0cd-2da0559098c9", "value": "The act of making a hole using a boring or rotating mechanism. Drilling can be associated with activities such as Oil extraction and the sinking of well systems."}

{"id": "35e7ba4c-2c23-4590-8d30-93957ff50c00", "value": "The act of rebuilding an archaeological site or a place which has been damaged or destroyed to its known and earlier state. In reconstruction a mixture or additional \"modern\" and new materials and techniques are used and it is distinguished from Restoration by this use of new materials."}
{"id": "61acf357-a3ad-4631-b608-c7c09a8570f8", "value": "A track or network of tracks along which a train runs. Usually composed of a series of steel rails running along the ground."}

{"id": "a695a6e3-401b-409c-a6e4-de85ebc6cd0f", "value": "A natural act involving an overflow from a water body, beyond its normal limits. This can lead to archaeological features being covered or submerged under a body of water. This term is differentiated from inundation"}

{"id": "34b3da47-d7dc-4cdc-8244-1c14c3f1d074", "value": "The act of trying to prevent or limit the loss of archaeological material using scientific methods. This does not cover actions or processes that attempt to maintain access to or create walkways etc. as a way of maintaining archaeological sites for tourism etc. "}
{"id": "a982256d-bf95-4362-be9a-43f10d593736", "value": "The act of firing or letting off small scale weaponry e.g. guns as opposed to the use of artillery."}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "cc92d0f8-2ee8-4772-946f-1babe9ce4e68", "value": "The act of deliberate breaking and damage of heritage "}

{"id": "3bbccc26-58a8-42d7-af1a-6fc1a51d05b5", "value": "Lack of upkeep activities, and legal frameworks (e.g legal enforcement of protection of heritage places) to look after sites. This category also includes lack of tourism and management strategies (such as the lack of human and financial resources and conservation plan, etc.) on a heritage site."}
{"id": "a4b10c16-1214-49be-bc2c-25293ce2848d", "value": "Invasion/inhabitation by living organisms in numbers or quantities large enough to be harmful. This includes burrowing."}

skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "571a7761-aecb-4e4b-a6fc-0767805eee67", "value": "A general term for the weatherproof coat on the external and internal walls of a building. It can be used both as protective and decorative layer."}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "7844257b-adb4-45a9-b939-3db92f23d29b", "value": "deliberate destruction or damage of heritage (includes religious / ethnic conflicts) "}

{"id": "41cdf085-f0ca-409a-90be-5d5116d8bce9", "value": "Photographs taken from an aircraft or flying object (e.g. fixed-wing aircraft, helicopters, UAVs, kites). This category applies only to raw, unprocessed photographs."}

{"id": "051c2567-70a8-4d6b-ae05-1e073ec4a555", "value": "The limiting of movement into and around an archaeological site. This can be due to activities such as inundation, as well as occupation/use of the site for military purposes."}
{"id": "4d0ccf3e-dec8-4c61-be52-1c2c4267d5d4", "value": "Impact on visual integrity, potential loss of aesthetic value"}

{"id": "de500ede-32b5-4a5c-ac07-3c7c1e8dd0d0", "value": "The deliberate removal and relocation of archaeological features from one site to another. This may be done to protect archaeological features (e.g. prevent its destruction via inundation etc.) or for other reasons."}

{"id": "28957981-c3bc-4d41-a813-3dc300a5cf87", "value": "Deposits burying/concealing features of archaeological significance, this can include the effects of sedimentation, rock falls, dumping of non-local material and/or the erection of new buildings or structures. This could be also caused by vegetation/tree cover. It also covers sites that are only partially covered."}
{"id": "38af0e24-7468-4280-a9a4-9dc0fbbc3ab6", "value": "The pressing or packing down of archaeological sites/artefacts/soils and so the material becomes flattened and/or compressed."}

{"id": "e4dc983b-d7f8-4681-bb71-2c43d27d05ad", "value": "Damage or alteration to an archaeological site/feature where the result does not cause the feature to become structurally unsound/compromised."}
{"id": "8d828d73-fce1-411c-9aac-fba7aeed7388", "value": "Detachment of Plaster (renders) or preparatory layer and paint layer or surface finishing "}

{"id": "a639ac88-1ed2-44ce-b9b4-373af6d9c332", "value": "Damage causing archaeological sites or features to fall in/subside or to become structually unsound, or the structural integrity of the site or feature to be compromised. This may include the partial or full demolition/destruction of a site or feature. This category includes structural deformation, inclination and swelling. "}

{"id": "27b8f454-0d0e-46e8-a50f-1e3c2756a593", "value": "The process of archaeological material being worn away/weathered, often due to natural causes (exposure to wind, rain, sunlight, as well as salt crystalization, insects and pests damage, and growth of micro organism). "}

{"id": "26ca4223-e5ee-4ea8-9fb3-93b90d57cfbb", "value": "Cracks will occur as a result of stress to structures. Cracks that occur within a limited/small area will not cause structural instability, however from fractures rainwater enters the structure and also plants and vegetation are often starts to grow-out resulting into structural damage and destabilisation. Recording and monitoring of cracks is an important step to understand whether they are enlarging or any deformation is in progress. "}

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "e03f3f7f-4105-4786-8418-018687c57e04", "value": "Loss of Intangible Heritage Linked to Heritage Resource"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "65a8d67e-67dd-462a-ab94-4180d2f80013", "value": "The removal of archaeological material from a site, often resulting from activities such as looting or archaeological excavation."}

{"id": "8d0f701e-d53b-4e6e-a071-944ce38312ec", "value": "Changes in the shape/form of landforms or the topography of a site as the result of activities, such as the bulldozing/dumping of non-local material. "}
{"id": "e13f1d67-cee7-4e57-b655-9717d242ee05", "value": "The drainage/percolation of harmful chemicals/waste materials into the soils of an archaeological site."}

{"id": "b4fce04b-14a7-4942-9dbf-ff419acc3bf1", "value": "The dispersal/spread of archaeological material/objects across the surface or subsurface of an archaeological site. This is often the result of ploughing."}
{"id": "fc3e94a7-afd6-4e4c-9317-1f15ab0b8033", "value": "The movement of earth/soil, not necessarily leading to the alteration of landforms and/or the burial of archaeological sites."}

{"id": "01243b6a-33f2-40d8-9f39-808534b7e3ad", "value": "The damage caused to archaeological sites/features via fire. This can include both damage caused by the flames of the fire, as well as smoke damage."}
{"id": "09329501-51f6-490c-b139-34b70c92eb76", "value": "A laser rangefinder is a rangefinder which uses a laser beam to determine the distance to an object."}
{"id": "7df5b8d1-e079-49c4-9bc6-18aafb4266fe", "value": "A researcher connected to a university or other institute of higher education"}
{"id": "df88deab-4c9c-4236-b22b-24cb6830e461", "value": "Someone who is not renumerated for their work"}

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "8cd2ca03-13e8-456e-bf40-649a54513519", "value": "Bronze Age, Susa IV/ Old Elamite I (Khuzestan)"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "5ee658ab-ad2d-46f9-a7e0-53a88a182733", "value": "\"vulnerability factors\" in glossary; \"vulnerability\" in RM; \"vulnerability_type.E55\" in dropdown list"}
{"id": "352bc9fb-7e86-4718-9b1a-449fa50e0df8", "value": "called Date of Next Assignment in the the Resource Manager"}

{"id": "e157cf3f-be67-41e5-9093-a16b7eb83c31", "value": "Saudi Commission for Tourism and National Heritage (SCTH)"}

{"id": "7ac9185a-0280-44eb-bc58-d3934b92d75f", "value": "Simple cleaning activities (e.g. formatting names, making sure there are no typos, etc.). Also includes reviewing (and if necessary) enhancing records of trainees or students."}

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "cd8d99b7-97b3-4a05-ac98-e286b491d933", "value": "Bronze Age, Susa V/ Old Elamite II (Khuzestan)"}
{"id": "f6859c59-be7e-490b-a468-068a2009fb86", "value": "is a non-contributor to / has as a non-contributor"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "53c8cf13-e195-4611-861c-22880087499d", "value": "Differential GPS or DGPS provide improved location accuracy down to as little as 10cm locational error. Each DGPS uses a network of fixed ground-based reference stations to broadcast the difference between the positions indicated by the GPS satellite system and known fixed positions."}

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "5d8f41fa-2097-43d7-8e19-074c1fb838c1", "value": "is an altered contributor to / has as a altered contributor"}
{"id": "b851cad9-6470-4425-9147-54961accc7ba", "value": "Bronze Age, Susa VI/ Old Elamite III (Khuzestan)"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "17c36b38-f188-4050-9f3b-6855c83c0c7c", "value": "Field title is called 'Condition Remarks', but field label looks like a repeat of 'Overall State'..."}

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "2dd58f18-5a7d-4f3d-9c3b-c0b97a667c98", "value": "is a contributor to / has as a contributor"}
{"id": "6331ae33-db2e-4993-a890-d0eb8ab025a2", "value": "is a potential contributor to / has as a possible contributor"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "143d3e10-6c18-41b5-83dc-8a798c0b7722", "value": "Photographs taken from an aircraft or flying object (e.g. fixed-wing aircraft, helicopters, UAVs, kites). This category applies only to processed photographs. Processing may include georectification and orthorectification."}
{"id": "16173503-f889-42dd-824a-7d8157f2f0e3", "value": "Satellite imagery provided via a 3D virtual globe model (Google Earth) or an online mapping services (e.g. Bing Maps)"}

{"id": "fc8d64df-bdc9-4970-a9a1-107847b361e9", "value": "Measurement derived from the analysis of satellite or aerial imagery (e.g. Google Earth, georectified satellite imagery and aerial photography)"}
{"id": "6cc32406-6061-4b9d-8d39-588c543742a0", "value": "For where you have an accurate reading, but no record what method was used"}

{"id": "49170af1-547f-4718-b5d5-875153351cd2", "value": "Archaeological field survey incorporates a range of methods leading to the detection, identification and documentation of the material traces of past human activity. Survey collects information about the location, distribution and organisation of past human cultures across a given study area. Excavation is the exposure, processing and recording of archaeological remains. Survey generally proceeds and complements excavation, and is external and horizontal in extent whereas excavation is internal and vertical."}

{"id": "4abbcb07-cf22-4617-9b95-149a69ea4016", "value": "A total station (TS) or total station theodolite (TST) is an electronic/optical instrument used for surveying and building construction.
